A-priori power analysis

library(powerly)

true_model <- generate_model(
    type = "ggm",
    nodes = 43,
    density = .05)

results <- powerly(
    range_lower = 300,
    range_upper = 700,
    samples = 30,
    replications = 40,
    measure = "sen",
    statistic = "power",
    measure_value = .7,
    statistic_value = .8,
    model = "ggm",
    model_matrix = true_model,
    cores = 5,
    verbose = TRUE)
## 
## Method run completed (46.3872 sec):
##  - converged: yes
##  - iterations: 1
##  - recommendation: 300
plot(results)

Network accuracy

We plot Bootstrapped edge CI’s - here we focus on large discrepancies between the red (observed values) and black (bootstrapped mean) lines. We can also look at the size of CI’s with larger grey areas showing less confidence

Dylan_plot_boot <- plot(Db1, labels = F, order = "sample")
Dylan_plot_boot
